There’s nothing worse than hauling a bag that’s half your weight out of taxis, across busy streets or up hotel stairs. Declutter your holiday and streamline your travel bag with this one ingenious trick. Our lives are rushed and cluttered, which is why your much-needed December holiday should be as stress-free as possible. That applies as much to the contents of your bag as to the actual planning of the trip. With this one tried-and-tested packing trick, you can minimise the items in your bag and essentially halve its weight. This trick is so simple it may seem obvious, but it’s still easy to miss. It is tempting to toss your favourite clothing items in the general direction of your bag before battling to zip them all in. But don’t. Take a breather and approach your cupboard with purpose. This time you’re going to apply a simple trick: you’re going to pack by outfit. Packing by outfit means laying out all your outfits before packing them into your bag. It will help you only take along clothing that can be mixed and matched. Here’s how it’s done: The beauty of travelling light is that there’s more space for holiday shopping. There are zero fees when you use your Capitec credit card at any Mastercard card machine worldwide or make bookings online. Travelling overseas? There are no currency conversion fees for international payments either. For more inspiration to simplify your life, follow us on Instagram or sign up to receive our weekly newsletter. This article was published in partnership with Capitec.